Do I Anticipate Issues When Testing Scripts?

Short Answer:
No major blockers If executing in the intended environment (Windows workstation with sufficient permissions and audit logging enabled).

Assumptions the scripts rely on:
	•	Audit logs are available (4624 events present in Security Log)
	•	PowerShell 5+ is running with admin rights
	•	Required modules (like ImportExcel, CimCmdlets) can be installed from PSGallery
	•	Get-WinEvent has sufficient access and returns data within the expected range
	•	Profiles aren’t corrupted or cleaned by group policy or disk cleanup

If any of the above are blocked by domain policy or third-party endpoint management, results will degrade or silently fail (e.g. no data returned).

Mitigations:
	•	Run Get-WinEvent -LogName Security -MaxEvents 1 manually first
	•	Run each module (e.g. Get-UserProfiles, Describe-ProfileState) standalone before orchestration
	•	Verify a workstation is holding 30 days’ worth of audit logs


