Prompting Improvements for Enterprise-Level Engineering

If you’re looking to step it up further, here are enterprise prompt refinements:

1. Layered Instruction Prompts

Instead of asking “fix this”, say:

**“Refactor this script for enterprise auditing:
	•	Harden against missing event logs
	•	Support remote workstation input
	•	Include a summary HTML dashboard header
	•	All output goes to /Output/YYYY-MM-DD/ folder with timestamped files”**

That guides the logic at multiple levels — security, structure, output, format.

⸻

2. Prompting for GitOps Integration

Use:

“Rebuild this to output GitOps-compliant reports, with changelog summary, Markdown README update, and a make audit-logon CLI trigger.”

You’ll automatically get Git-aware outputs, report names like logon-2025-05-26.csv, and changelog logic baked in.

⸻

3. Feedback-Informed Regeneration

If you’re unhappy with a script’s output:

“Refactor the following output to follow a logging-first, modular-first architecture. Add hooks for telemetry and compliance integration.”

That adds structure beyond the logic itself.

⸻

4. Test-Aware Prompting

When running pre-CAB:

“Generate a risk matrix and test plan for this PowerShell script. Include log paths, expected outcomes, false positive conditions, and rollback triggers.”

I’ll respond with a structured grid showing:
	•	Test objective
	•	What will pass/fail look like
	•	Log path
	•	Risk rating


